     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. The project has prepared overview of best practices on implementation of CEDAW concluding observations and best practices on reporting to CEDAW. The overview report covers:
a) overview of world indices and ranking related to gender equality, overview of gender related indicators of developed countries;
b) best practices on reporting to CEDAW;
c) overview and classification of CEDAW recommendations given to Uzbekistan.
Project is also studying the national reports and process of collecting information on national reporting to CEDAW Committee in order to reveal human rights indicators related to CEDAW reporting that were used in previous reports. The results of these studies will be used in preparation of draft decision on national reporting to CEDAW with clear indication of human rights related indicators as well as responsibilities and contribution of relevant government authorities into the CEDAW draft report.
2. Project supported to translation of OHCHR publication national mechanisms of reporting and follow up into Uzbek and submitted to NHRC.
On 10 December 2018 President adopted resolution on improving the work of National human rights center1, according to which NHRC has become state body that ensures interactions of state bodies and other organizations on implementation of international obligations of the Republic of Uzbekistan and preparation of national reports in the field of human rights. This decision will be reflected in revision of concept note of human rights course for personnel of NHRC that Project has prepared and submitted for review on national partner. Moreover, the Project is working on elaboration of new website for NHRC that will also reflects provisions of new resolution on NHRC.
With the view to provide technical support to NHRC and other national partners in enhancing capacities in reporting to UN Treaty Bodies on human rights and follow up to their recommendations, the project translated and edited 6 human rights and SDGs related publications of OHCHR and IPU into Uzbek. Among them are: The Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities: Training Guide No. 19, 2014; National Mechanisms for Reporting and Follow-up: A Practical Guide to Effective State Engagement with International Human Rights Mechanisms &#x431; 2016; Human Rights. Handbook for Parliamentarians N&#xB0; 26, 2016; Reporting to the United Nations Human Rights Treaty Bodies training guide. Part I &#x2013; Manual, 2017; Parliaments and SDGs: self- assessment toolkit, 2016
3. Follow up to UPR/Treaty Bodies recommendations UPR project conducted joint briefings for public awareness raising on the results of the consideration of Uzbekistan&#x2019;s report on the human rights situation during the third cycle of the UPR in Geneva and Tashkent; contributed to preparation of policy paper with recommendation on approaches (and expediency) of ratification and implementation of UN CRPD that was drafted by RIA Project; and prepared policy papers on national preventive mechanism, compliance of national legislation with UNCAT and expediency of ratification of UN OPCAT. Moreover, following the recommendation of UN Treaty Bodies on application of provisions of UN Treaties by Courts UPR Project jointly with RoL Project supported in preparation of Joint action Plan of NHRC and Supreme Court on application of UN Treaties by courts within this plan UPR Project also initiated comparative analysis on compliance of national legislation with article of 19 of UN ICCPR in part of access of information , and prepared handbook for informational and press services of state bodies on ensuring the rights on access to information.</narrative>
